Package: githubtools
Title: Tools for building and using GitHub pkgs.
Version: 0.0.0.9100
Authors@R: person("Jonathan", "Carroll", email = "jono@jcarroll.com.au", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a suite of tools to complement packages stored on or
    loaded from GitHub. When building a package, this provides a Rmd macro to insert
    a HTML popup bar in the help menu linking back to the GitHub project page to
    encourage collaboration. Also able to scan the user's R library for packages
    installed from GitHub, analyse their commit frequency, and report back.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.3.0)
License: GPL (>=3)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: TRUE
Imports:
    magrittr,
    dplyr,
    github,
    lubridate,
    ggplot2
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
Remotes: 
  jonocarroll/htmlhelp
